    schema1:description "Simon Chesterman joined the Civil Nuclear Constabulary in January 2014 as the CNC ’s deputy chief constable and was promoted to chief constable on 1 April 2019. He is also the National Police Chiefs’ Council lead expert on armed policing. He began his career with Thames Valley Police and went on to become deputy chief constable, specialist operations, West Mercia Police . In 2012 he was awarded the Queen’s Police Medal."@en ;
    schema1:name "Simon Chesterman OBE, QPM"@en ;
